cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with content caching on the edge of 5G networks for connected cars. Other likely sub-categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the paper proposes a caching scheme for edge nodes, cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper discusses the protocols through which different system entities can interact, cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper proposes a complete system architecture, and cs.MM (Multimedia) as the paper assesses the performance of the proposed approach against state-of-the-art solutions.
